review_blob: The bottle is the part of this beer. Buy one if only to add a bottle to your bar shelf.

Bottle from Kensington Wine Market Calgary.
Wicked sour. Strong oak aromas with tanic cherry flavour. Good but I like very very sour - might be a bit much...
beer_name: Birrificio del Ducato La Luna Rossa

review_blob:
Great Gueuze. First example that was blended from several brewers that I have tried. Everything that I look for was here. Spritzy citrus, plenty of dry funk, wet basement and barny taste. For the price it may well be my go to gueuze.
Bottle from Kensington Wine Market in Calgary.

Sample from bottle.Pours clear with minimal head with no retention. Nice looking in the glass, but this is where everthing goea down hill. Aroma is strong apricots athat overpower anything else. Taste is sickly sweet fruit. I hesitate to call this a beer... More so a cooler.

Amber colour with very thin white head that disappears very quickly with no lacing. Aroma is clearlt cascade with a grassy under tone. Taste is thin and light, nice bittering, but malt is very light. Overall okay IPA, but not worth having another.
